│ THOUGHT: The global disabling of NUW on trunc caused other tests to fail because InstCombine relies on setting NUW when it's provably safe. The miscompile arises specifically when the  │
│ source has range metadata: setting NUW on trunc in that case can introduce poison. Therefore, I will adjust the NUW-setting condition to avoid setting NUW if the source operand has     │
│ range metadata, while keeping the optimization for other cases.                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '949,952s/if (!Trunc.hasNoUnsignedWrap() &&/if (!Trunc.hasNoUnsignedWrap() && !Src->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_range) &&/' llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCasts.cpp  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
